# 4. もっと強く

Honami: (Let's see... The CD Shiho recommended should be...)
Honami: (Oh, here it is! Thank goodness I found it.)
Honami: (She said it should help me because their drummer's very good. I'll try listening to it while I practice, starting today.)
Honami: Huh...?
Honami: (These are our CDs...! And they're on display in a prime location...!)
Honami: Hehe. I'll tell the others about this later...
???: Hey, did you listen to that song?
???: Yeah, it was so good! Got any others that you recommend?
???: Yeah, wanna check out my playlist later?
???: Cool! Thanks!
Honami: ...!
Honami: (Those voices. They sounded like...)
Honami's Former Classmate C: But I haven't been listening to much music lately because I'm spending so much time studying...
Honami: (It is them...!)
Honami's Classmate C: You act chummy with just about anyone. Whose side are you on?
Honami: ...
Honami: (Oh... I couldn't help but hide from them...)
Honami's Former Classmate A: Oh!
Honami's Former Classmate A: Hey, have you two heard of this band? They're called Leo/need! I just discovered them recently and they're pretty good!
Honami: ...!
Honami's Former Classmate B: Yeah, I've heard of them! Also, isn't Honami in this band?
Honami's Former Classmate A: What?! She is?!
Honami's Former Classmate A: She's in a band...? And she's gone pro?
Honami: (They're talking about Leo/need.)
Honami: (What do I do...?)
Honami: (I'm afraid that they're going to say some really mean things about me again...)
Honami's Former Classmate B: I'm curious as to what this song's like. I might give it a listen.
Honami's Former Classmate B: Still, it's hard to believe that Honami's in a band. I didn't think she was the type.
Honami: ...
Honami's Former Classmate C: I mean, does that matter? She's clearly doing her best.
Honami's Former Classmate C: Also, I've already had a chance to listen to this song. I thought it was pretty good.
Honami: Huh...?
Honami's Former Classmate A: Yeah, true. It is a good song.
Honami's Former Classmate B: Do you know who else is in Leo/need besides Honami?
Honami's Former Classmate C: Pretty sure they're all Honami's childhood friends. Like Hoshino and...
Honami: ...
Honami: (I...)
Honami: (I... In that moment...)
Honami: (What do I do...?)
Honami: (I'm afraid that they're going to say some really mean things about me again...)
Honami: ...!
Honami: Huff... Huff...
Honami: (This is bad... My mind keeps jumping back to that moment.)
Honami: (I know I can't keep going on like this...)
MEIKO: You seem more motivated than usual today.
Honami: MEIKO...!
Honami: I'm sorry for not noticing you sooner...
MEIKO: That's okay. More importantly...
MEIKO: Did something happen to you?
Honami: Huh? H-How did you know...?
MEIKO: The way you were drumming sounded a little different.
Honami: The way I was drumming...?
MEIKO: Yes. It seemed like you were trying very hard to sound energized, but you thrashed around quite a bit...
Honami: That's...
MEIKO: I'll be happy to listen. I am a senior you look up to, after all.
Honami: Hehe... Thank you very much.
Honami: The thing is...
Honami: I was at the CD shop earlier and just happened to see my old classmates from junior high school.
MEIKO: From junior high school? Wasn't that when...?
Honami: Yes... I don't have too many fond memories from back then...
Honami: And I ended up hiding from them.
MEIKO: You hid?
Honami: Yes, behind some shelves...
Honami: Then, they saw our CDs and I overheard them talking about us...
Honami: I became so worried that they would say some more awful things about me.
Honami: But that wasn't what happened at all...
MEIKO: Go on...
Honami: Then, I...
Honami: I felt so weak.
MEIKO: Weak...?
Honami: I ran and hid because I didn't want to hear them talking about me behind my back again...
Honami: Even though it was partially my fault that we ended up arguing with each other.
Honami: I immediately jumped to the conclusion that they were going to say mean things about me. Even when I found out that wasn't the case, I wasn't able to go over and talk to them...
MEIKO: ...
Honami: Now that we're professional musicians, I know that we'll be faced with various challenges moving forward.
Honami: We may need to be even more courageous than when we stood up to Mr. Shindo.
Honami: As the leader of this band, it's my duty to learn how to pull us in the right direction.
Honami: Which is why I want to become stronger...
MEIKO: I see...
MEIKO: I understand why you felt that you were weak in that moment, Honami...
MEIKO: But I believe that you've become such a strong girl.
Honami: Huh...?
MEIKO: When we first met, Honami, you had so much on your mind and were very indecisive, remember?
Honami: Oh... Yes, I remember.
MEIKO: I know it's hard for you to get a good sense of this...
MEIKO: But you've gradually been getting stronger. You're much more decisive now, and have the courage to speak your mind.
MEIKO: So, I think you should just keep doing your best and not get too anxious.
Honami: MEIKO...
Honami: Thank you very much. I feel a little bit better now.
MEIKO: Hehe. I'm glad I could help a little.
MEIKO: Oh, that's right... This seems like a nice place to stop and get a change of scenery. Would you like to join me?
Honami: Huh? A change of scenery?
MEIKO: Yes! A rather interesting place just appeared in SEKAI...
